    • Constructor Detail

      • Token

        public Token(java.lang.String accessToken,
             java.lang.String tokenType,
             int expiresIn,
             java.lang.String refreshToken,
             java.lang.String scopeString,
             java.util.List<? extends com.adamratzman.spotify.SpotifyScope> scopes)

        Represents a Spotify Token, retrieved through instantiating a SpotifyAPI

        Parameters:
        accessToken - An access token that can be provided in subsequent calls,for example to Spotify Web API services.
        tokenType - How the access token may be used: always “Bearer”.
        expiresIn - The time period (in seconds) for which the access token is valid.
        refreshToken - A token that can be sent to the Spotify Accounts service in place of an authorization code,null if the token was created using a method that does not support token refresh
        scopes - A list of scopes granted access for this accessToken. Anempty list means that the token can only be used to acces public information.
        See Also:
        SpotifyAPI
